{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} '''Francesco Dattaro''' (c. 1495 &ndash; 1576) and his son '''Giuseppe Dattaro''' (c. 1540 &ndash; 1616), are the two principal builders of the most important family of [[Cremona|Cremonese]] architects of the fifteenth century. The Dattaros began their activity at the construction site of the [[Cathedral of Cremona]], joining the painters, members of the cabinet making Sacca family, and the engineer [[Antonio Melone]].
