{{distinguish|Xiao Yang (governor)}} {{no footnotes|date=February 2015}} {{Chinese name|[[Xiao (surname)|Xiao]]}} {{Infobox president | image = | image_size = 150px | name = Xiao Yang | caption = | office = President of the [[Supreme People's Court of China]] | term_start = 1998 | term_end = 2008 | predecessor = [[Ren Jianxin]] | successor = [[Wang Shengjun]] | birth_name = | birth_date = August 1938 | birth_place = [[Heyuan]], [[Guangdong]] | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = Chinese | party = [[Communist Party of China]] | spouse = | children = | relatives = | footnotes = }} '''Xiao Yang''' ({{zh|s=肖扬|t=蕭揚|p=Xiāo Yáng|j=Chiu3 Yeung4}}; born August 1938 in [[Heyuan]], [[Guangdong]]) is a Chinese judge and politician who served as Minister of Justice and President of the [[Supreme People's Court of China]].
==Biography== He received his LL.B degree from [[Renmin University of China Law School]] in 1962.
Xiao Yang was the [[Minister of Justice]] from 1993 to 1998. He was elected as the President of the Supreme People's Court in 1998 to replace [[Ren Jianxin]] and was re-elected in 2003 for the second term.
Xiao Yang was a member of the [[15th CPC Central Committee|15th]] and [[16th CPC Central Committee]].
